column1: ## comments and empty lines in this file are ignored.  Two columns
## (space or tab-delimited) specify the barcode id and the bardcode
## itself.  A lower case letter in the barcode means: this letter must
## *always* be exact.  This can be used if some barcodes are not
## different enough from the other to allow a fixed number of
## mismatches.  The current version fixes problems with insufficient
## edit distance in the previous versions, and is safe to use while
## allowing for a one nucleotide mismatch.
## The IDs of the barcodes are those of the wells, counting by row
## (i.e. A1-A24, B1-B24, ... , P1-P24) version v3 of this file uses
## sequential names (c1-c384), but is otherwise identical.
